  "last_post_content": "Bridging development and operations delivers value faster. Here's the signal.\n\nThe thing nobody tells engineers about building influence as a devops engineer:\n\nTeams often find that building influence requires more than just technical skills. Production experience shows that devops engineers need to develop strong communication and collaboration skills to effectively influence others. This can be a significant career milestone, as it requires a shift from focusing solely on technical expertise to also considering the social and organizational aspects of the role.\n\nThe data shows that several strategies can help devops engineers build influence, including:\n\u2022 Establishing a strong track record of delivering high-quality work\n\u2022 Developing a deep understanding of the organization's goals and priorities\n\u2022 Building relationships with key stakeholders and decision-makers\n\nThe reality is that many devops engineers make common mistakes, such as focusing too much on technical details and not enough on the broader organizational context. Evidence suggests that taking a more holistic approach can help devops engineers avoid these mistakes and build greater influence.\n\nResources such as industry blogs and conferences can provide valuable information and insights for devops engineers looking to build influence. The timeline for building influence can vary, but experience reveals that it often takes several months to a year or more to establish a strong reputation and build trust with key stakeholders.\n\nWhat career advice would you add? Share your experience below.\n\n#cloudengineering #sre #infrastructure #mlops #devops",
